  "metadata": {
    "source": "TYPTI Rankings Cheat Sheet.pdf (2026-06-03)",
    "verifiedAgainst": "TYPTI US Open Championships 2026 (tournament 8d28f967-d40c-4062-8081-f2f7b33673a5) — 33/33 PDF cheat-sheet rows matched",
    "notes": [
      "Levels mirror PDF 'TYPTI Ranking Points Table': L1 MAJOR (2000W), L2 PREMIER (1000W), L3 OPEN (500W), L4 CHALLENGER (250W), L5 CLASSIC (125W).",
      "Per-round decay (% of winner): W 100, RU 65, SF-3rd 45, SF-4th 35, QF 20, R16 10, R32 5, R64 2.5, R128 1.",
      "Draw-size scaling: 16+ entrants 100%, 12-15 75%, 8-11 50%, 4-7 25%, <4 0%. Encoded as threshold conditions in the value arrays; first matching threshold wins. drawSize=15 hits the 11-threshold (75%); drawSize=16 hits the 15-threshold (100%); drawSize<4 falls through to 0.",
      "Doubles teams: both partners receive full team points (doublesAttribution: fullToEach).",
      "Backdraw/consolation finishes do not earn ranking points: the profile lists only MAIN and PLAY_OFF stages. PLAY_OFF stage covers TODS 3rd-place / placement playoffs, which the PDF DOES award points for; CONSOLATION stage (true backdraw) is excluded.",
      "Mixed Doubles gender split (man's portion -> Men's MX, woman's portion -> Women's MX) is enforced at ranking-list-generation time via category/gender filtering, not in the award profile.",
      "No 3rd/4th playoff edge case: PDF specifies both semis get 40% of winner when no playoff is held. The factory's finishingPositionRange mechanism cannot disambiguate the no-playoff case from the playoff-loser case at the value layer; both currently resolve to position 4 = 35%. If you need the 40% bonus, generate the playoff structure (factory creates it automatically on draw generation when policy specifies a 3rd/4th playoff)."
    ]
  }
